  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "It is indeed the case that AI polls can be opaque, and their output not easily explainable by auditing the input data.",
    "Explicability is a necessary precondition to hold AI pollsters accountable, as is the case for any novel AI (Floridi and Cowls 2022).",
    "Explicability can help foster trust between AI pollsters and the public at large (Papagni et al. 2023), which is necessary to realise its democratic value.",
    "This is the criterion we need to satisfy, in order to protect against the manipulation objection.",
    "We can identify two specific risks that make this novel technology uniquely inexplicable: (1) the use of unrepresentative samples, under the promise that AI can fully adjust for sample biases; (2) the inability to interpret the models used to generate predictions, largely due to their complexity."
